1
00:00:12,280 --> 00:00:14,320
♪ You're the only one in my heart ♪

2
00:00:14,320 --> 00:00:16,000
♪ Even if you never know ♪

3
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:19,840
♪ I'll keep watching over you ♪

4
00:00:19,840 --> 00:00:23,760
♪ I love you more than words
but our path isn't easy ♪

5
00:00:23,760 --> 00:00:27,040
♪ I just need you to believe in me ♪

6
00:00:27,080 --> 00:00:30,720
♪ I'm weak for your lips ♪

7
00:00:30,720 --> 00:00:34,480
♪ And the kiss upon my forehead ♪

8
00:00:34,480 --> 00:00:41,480
♪ Every action conveys these words, you know? ♪

9
00:00:41,560 --> 00:00:44,960
♪ Can you hear me saying I love you? ♪

10
00:00:44,960 --> 00:00:47,000
♪ Use the feeling you know ♪

11
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:51,120
♪ And you'll love so deeply ♪

12
00:00:51,120 --> 00:00:55,120
♪ Can you feel my love? ♪

13
00:00:55,120 --> 00:01:00,400
♪ Please know that I love you ♪

14
00:01:16,920 --> 00:01:20,640
♪ In the moments when we look at each other ♪

15
00:01:20,640 --> 00:01:23,560
♪ Even if I don't say it out loud ♪

16
00:01:23,560 --> 00:01:27,200
♪ Deep inside, I only care about you ♪

17
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:30,680
♪ Love is so magical ♪

18
00:01:32,440 --> 00:01:34,000
Don't say anything.

19
00:01:35,680 --> 00:01:38,560
♪ And there aren't many sweet words ♪

20
00:01:38,560 --> 00:01:41,040
Just listen to my heartbeat.

21
00:01:41,920 --> 00:01:45,440
♪ Will always be you ♪

22
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:49,280
♪ I'm weak for your lips ♪

23
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:53,280
♪ And the kiss upon my forehead ♪

24
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:59,760
♪ Every action conveys these words, you know? ♪

25
00:02:00,040 --> 00:02:03,800
♪ Can you hear me saying I love you? ♪

26
00:02:03,800 --> 00:02:07,600
♪ My love is in these soft whispers ♪

27
00:02:07,600 --> 00:02:09,919
♪ You have to feel it with your heart ♪

28
00:02:09,919 --> 00:02:15,120
♪ Our touches will make you understand ♪

29
00:02:15,120 --> 00:02:18,520
♪ Can you hear me saying I love you? ♪

30
00:02:18,520 --> 00:02:20,920
♪ Use the feeling you know ♪

31
00:02:20,920 --> 00:02:24,600
♪ And you'll love so deeply ♪

32
00:02:24,600 --> 00:02:28,640
♪ Can you feel my love? ♪

33
00:02:28,640 --> 00:02:32,720
♪ Please know that I love you ♪

34
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:39,320
Can I be the one setting the rhythm tonight?

35
00:02:42,280 --> 00:02:43,320
Mm-hmm.

36
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:47,920
♪ You're the only one in my heart ♪

37
00:02:47,920 --> 00:02:49,560
♪ Even if you never know ♪

38
00:02:49,560 --> 00:02:53,360
♪ I'll keep watching over you ♪

39
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:57,280
♪ I love you more than words
but our path isn't easy ♪

40
00:02:57,280 --> 00:03:00,600
♪ I just need you to believe in me ♪

41
00:03:00,600 --> 00:03:04,280
♪ I'm weak for your lips ♪

42
00:03:04,280 --> 00:03:08,040
♪ And the kiss upon my forehead ♪

43
00:03:08,040 --> 00:03:15,040
♪ Every action conveys these words, you know? ♪

44
00:03:15,080 --> 00:03:18,800
♪ Can you hear me saying I love you? ♪

45
00:03:18,840 --> 00:03:22,600
♪ My love is in these soft whispers ♪

46
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:31,320
MOM

47
00:03:52,480 --> 00:03:53,600
Yes, Mom?

48
00:03:57,280 --> 00:03:58,200
What?

49
00:03:58,640 --> 00:03:59,840
You're at the gate?

50
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:06,480
Why didn't you tell me you were coming?

51
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:08,280
What if I wasn't home?

52
00:04:08,600 --> 00:04:12,400
So what? If you're not home,
I can leave the stuff with the maid.

53
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:15,800
Don't worry about me talking to your wife.

54
00:04:15,840 --> 00:04:17,720
Not that I want to, anyway.

55
00:04:17,760 --> 00:04:18,839
Mom…

56
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:20,920
So where is she?

57
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:26,280
It's a holiday. Neen's still sleeping.

58
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:30,640
If you hadn't come, I'd still be in the bed too.

59
00:04:31,280 --> 00:04:32,920
Since when do you sleep in, huh?

60
00:04:36,640 --> 00:04:38,320
Well… do you want to eat with us?

61
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:42,400
Thanks, but I already ate with your dad.

62
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:45,360
Do you want this now? I can heat it up.
It'll only take a minute.

63
00:04:45,360 --> 00:04:46,760
-It's okay, Mom.
-Oh?

64
00:04:47,200 --> 00:04:48,520
I can do it myself.

65
00:04:48,520 --> 00:04:49,840
It's nothing, honey.

66
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:53,360
It's your day off. You should rest.

67
00:04:53,360 --> 00:04:54,840
I'll take care of it.

68
00:04:54,840 --> 00:04:57,720
If your wife won't take care of you, I will.

69
00:04:58,120 --> 00:05:00,280
Neen works too, you know.

70
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:04,360
Besides, it's not her job to take care of me.

71
00:05:04,680 --> 00:05:08,000
I don't expect her to do everything alone.

72
00:05:08,360 --> 00:05:09,240
Works?

73
00:05:09,440 --> 00:05:11,680
I doubt she works as hard as you do.

74
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:14,360
Has she ever done anything meaningful?

75
00:05:14,360 --> 00:05:17,160
All she does is lounge around in pretty dresses.

76
00:05:17,160 --> 00:05:19,640
Can you stop criticizing her like that?

77
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:24,000
Oh, Runch. You're blindly taking her side again.

78
00:05:24,400 --> 00:05:28,120
Would it kill you
to admit you chose the wrong partner?

79
00:05:29,520 --> 00:05:30,640
What's so wrong with me, Mother?

80
00:05:39,840 --> 00:05:44,120
Your daughter loves me very much, you know.

81
00:05:47,320 --> 00:05:48,600
Anyway…

82
00:05:49,240 --> 00:05:52,400
what are you doing in my house this early?

83
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:57,000
Is that how you greet people?

84
00:05:57,920 --> 00:06:00,760
And look at what you're wearing.
Like some pin-up girl.

85
00:06:00,760 --> 00:06:02,720
Did you run out of decent clothes?

86
00:06:04,040 --> 00:06:07,000
Is this how rich girls dress?

87
00:06:08,040 --> 00:06:10,480
I'm not really into this style, Mother.

88
00:06:11,320 --> 00:06:12,760
But Runch…

89
00:06:13,720 --> 00:06:16,720
she says it's easy to take off. She likes it.

90
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:17,720
Ugh!

91
00:06:18,200 --> 00:06:20,000
Shameless! Disgusting!

92
00:06:20,160 --> 00:06:21,480
That's enough, Mom.

93
00:06:23,160 --> 00:06:24,640
And you just woke up?

94
00:06:25,960 --> 00:06:29,160
If I hadn't come, my daughter would've starved.

95
00:06:29,280 --> 00:06:33,520
Oh, Mother. Your daughter can feed herself.

96
00:06:33,520 --> 00:06:35,080
And she can feed me too.

97
00:06:35,080 --> 00:06:37,520
Are you disabled or something?
Why does she have to do that for you?

98
00:06:37,640 --> 00:06:40,960
I'm not disabled, you know.

99
00:06:40,960 --> 00:06:44,200
But I'm Runch's little lovebug.

100
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:46,080
Oh my god!

101
00:06:46,520 --> 00:06:48,280
You're just letting her do that?!

102
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:52,080
Oh, she lets me do a lot more than this.

103
00:06:52,080 --> 00:06:55,160
She does everything I ask her to do.

104
00:06:55,320 --> 00:06:56,320
Right?

105
00:06:57,160 --> 00:07:00,200
You love taking orders from your wife, don't you?

106
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:01,160
Ah!

107
00:07:01,160 --> 00:07:02,760
I can't take this anymore!

108
00:07:02,760 --> 00:07:04,560
Enough, Mom! Just leave!

109
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:06,560
What?

110
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:08,360
You're kicking me out?

111
00:07:09,520 --> 00:07:11,000
I'm not kicking you out, Mom.

112
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:13,320
But you should go.

113
00:07:13,440 --> 00:07:15,480
Come on, I'll walk you out.

114
00:07:15,840 --> 00:07:16,720
Let's go.

115
00:07:17,280 --> 00:07:18,200
Come.

116
00:07:18,360 --> 00:07:19,320
You're insane!

117
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:20,480
Mom!

118
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:22,440
Why are you--

119
00:07:24,480 --> 00:07:25,440
-Ugh!
-Mom…

120
00:07:27,120 --> 00:07:30,200
What are you doing? Why are you kicking me out?

121
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:31,040
Mom…

122
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:33,200
Enough, please.

123
00:07:33,440 --> 00:07:38,000
This is exactly why I asked you
to let me know before coming over.

124
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:39,800
This is your house too.

125
00:07:40,160 --> 00:07:43,240
Why do I need to let you know
or ask for your permission before I come?

126
00:07:43,400 --> 00:07:45,360
Who told you it was mine?

127
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:49,440
Did you forget Neen's family
bought this house for both of us?

128
00:07:49,440 --> 00:07:51,840
So that's why she's so arrogant.

129
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:53,720
Enough, Mom.

130
00:07:54,160 --> 00:07:57,440
I don't want you coming here
because you're always like this.

131
00:07:57,960 --> 00:07:59,560
Your wife started it.

132
00:07:59,560 --> 00:08:03,320
No, Mom. Neen didn't start anything.

133
00:08:03,320 --> 00:08:04,040
Runch!

134
00:08:04,280 --> 00:08:05,080
Mom…

135
00:08:05,640 --> 00:08:08,440
just go, okay? Please.

136
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:09,960
Come on.

137
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:13,000
Fine. But I'm only leaving
because you asked me to.

138
00:08:50,080 --> 00:08:51,000
Neen…

139
00:08:51,920 --> 00:08:54,000
go change and come downstairs to eat, okay?

140
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:55,040
I'm not eating.

141
00:08:56,160 --> 00:08:57,280
You're not hungry?

142
00:08:57,520 --> 00:08:58,560
Just leave me alone.

143
00:09:00,040 --> 00:09:02,400
I own this house too, you know.

144
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:05,320
If you're bringing anyone over,
at least tell me first.

145
00:09:05,360 --> 00:09:08,760
I don't want that babbling hag coming in here
and cursing at me.

146
00:09:08,880 --> 00:09:10,200
This has been going on for way too long.

147
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:11,160
Neen!

148
00:09:11,920 --> 00:09:12,800
She's my mother.

149
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:13,800
So what?

150
00:09:14,680 --> 00:09:18,520
Am I supposed to just let her insult me?
Can't I insult her back?

151
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:22,760
Am I the only one
you're okay with getting insulted?

152
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:27,720
I'm sorry, okay?

153
00:09:28,480 --> 00:09:29,320
I'm sorry.

154
00:09:31,160 --> 00:09:32,720
You know how my mom is.

155
00:09:33,320 --> 00:09:35,160
She's hard to reason with.

156
00:09:35,880 --> 00:09:39,560
So you're trying to put me in my place instead?

157
00:09:50,720 --> 00:09:52,320
Aren't you tired of this?

158
00:09:53,880 --> 00:09:56,120
You two are always fighting.

159
00:09:57,840 --> 00:09:58,800
Of course I'm tired of it.

160
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:01,720
Honestly, I'm tired of you both.

161
00:10:02,280 --> 00:10:05,040
But you know why she's like this?

162
00:10:05,040 --> 00:10:07,760
Because you always let her do what she wants.

163
00:10:08,120 --> 00:10:10,480
When she does something rude or wrong,

164
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:12,160
things no decent person would do,

165
00:10:12,160 --> 00:10:14,080
that's when you should correct her.

166
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:18,200
And if you won't, then I will.

167
00:10:18,800 --> 00:10:21,680
All this constant fighting is exhausting, okay?

168
00:10:22,480 --> 00:10:25,120
I can't keep living like this.

169
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:28,960
She's the one who keeps insulting me!

170
00:10:28,960 --> 00:10:31,560
Your mother's like a rabid dog,

171
00:10:31,560 --> 00:10:33,880
and you still expect peace?

172
00:10:33,880 --> 00:10:34,720
Neen!

173
00:10:48,880 --> 00:10:49,920
I'm sorry.

174
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:51,200
I'm sorry.

175
00:10:52,520 --> 00:10:53,880
I didn't mean it.

176
00:10:54,840 --> 00:10:56,880
You're angry because I insulted her…

177
00:10:56,880 --> 00:10:59,800
Were you ever angry when she treated me like that?

178
00:11:04,880 --> 00:11:06,520
You're good at everything.

179
00:11:09,120 --> 00:11:10,560
Everyone admires you.

180
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:13,720
You're good and successful at your job.

181
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:18,120
To everyone else, you seem so perfect.

182
00:11:18,840 --> 00:11:20,000
But you know what?

183
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:23,920
As your wife and someone sharing a life with you,

184
00:11:23,920 --> 00:11:25,520
I think you're the worst person!

185
00:11:30,320 --> 00:11:31,480
I regret it.

186
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:34,360
I regret marrying you more than anything.

187
00:11:35,720 --> 00:11:38,760
If I could go back in time, I'd never do it.

188
00:11:43,120 --> 00:11:44,120
I'm sorry.

189
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:47,400
You said you wanted a divorce before.

190
00:11:47,960 --> 00:11:49,320
Now I want one too.

191
00:11:51,360 --> 00:11:53,360
But while we're still married,

192
00:11:53,920 --> 00:11:56,240
just try to be a decent partner…

193
00:11:56,760 --> 00:12:00,040
at least for this period,
as my family asked of you.

194
00:12:01,680 --> 00:12:03,600
Pretend we still love each other.

195
00:12:05,320 --> 00:12:09,800
Just once… make your mother choke
on how much we love each other.

196
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:12,080
Even if it's just for a short period of time

197
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:19,320
Neen…

198
00:12:52,960 --> 00:12:55,200
Are you both sure about this divorce?

199
00:12:56,080 --> 00:12:56,960
Yes.

200
00:12:57,120 --> 00:12:59,360
We've both agreed on it.

201
00:13:00,320 --> 00:13:04,000
I never thought I'd hear the two of you
say that so easily.

202
00:13:05,480 --> 00:13:06,960
You're both adults…

203
00:13:08,040 --> 00:13:09,240
and mature enough.

204
00:13:12,160 --> 00:13:13,240
But… fine.

205
00:13:14,360 --> 00:13:16,400
I trust you've thought this through.

206
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:22,440
I do have one request, though.

207
00:13:24,280 --> 00:13:25,520
And it's very important.

208
00:13:31,400 --> 00:13:34,840
For now, don't tell anyone about the divorce.

209
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:38,320
Not even your family, Runch.

210
00:13:39,880 --> 00:13:43,440
I want this to stay within our family.

211
00:13:44,960 --> 00:13:48,640
Iperis Group will open
its restaurants in four months.

212
00:13:49,960 --> 00:13:52,360
There'll be press coverage, business partners…

213
00:13:52,360 --> 00:13:54,960
This is a major event for our company and family.

214
00:13:56,520 --> 00:13:59,960
And for the press release, we need the image

215
00:14:00,280 --> 00:14:02,160
of a stable marriage.

216
00:14:04,680 --> 00:14:05,880
Just four months…

217
00:14:06,960 --> 00:14:08,360
Can you do that for me?

218
00:14:17,680 --> 00:14:18,520
Yes.

219
00:14:22,480 --> 00:14:23,440
Thank you.

220
00:14:25,040 --> 00:14:26,480
This won't be easy.

221
00:14:27,840 --> 00:14:29,200
But I promise you…

222
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:31,400
once these four months are over,

223
00:14:31,680 --> 00:14:33,760
whatever decision you make,

224
00:14:34,400 --> 00:14:36,000
I won't stand in your way.

225
00:15:00,760 --> 00:15:01,840
Natee…

226
00:15:02,640 --> 00:15:05,200
I think I really need to divorce Neen.

227
00:15:05,720 --> 00:15:06,600
Huh?

228
00:15:06,800 --> 00:15:07,720
Divorce?

229
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:09,320
Are you serious?

230
00:15:10,400 --> 00:15:11,880
That's huge.

231
00:15:12,160 --> 00:15:14,520
You two love each other so much. What happened?

232
00:15:15,120 --> 00:15:18,000
Every time my mom and Neen see each other,

233
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:22,360
I have to watch the two people I love

234
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:25,000
hurt each other over and over again.

235
00:15:26,040 --> 00:15:28,160
I want to protect both of them…

236
00:15:30,840 --> 00:15:32,320
But in the end,

237
00:15:32,720 --> 00:15:34,560
I can't do anything.

238
00:15:34,960 --> 00:15:36,880
I can't protect either of them.

239
00:15:37,840 --> 00:15:39,600
Neen's exhausted, you know.

240
00:15:39,840 --> 00:15:41,560
Part of it is work…

241
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:45,600
but she's exhausted because of me and my mom too.

242
00:15:46,360 --> 00:15:48,960
She keeps acting strong,

243
00:15:50,240 --> 00:15:53,400
even though she's actually really sensitive.

244
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:56,600
Every time my mom insults her…

245
00:15:58,120 --> 00:16:00,920
the look in her eyes…

246
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:04,200
It's like a hurt child with nowhere to go.

247
00:16:05,040 --> 00:16:07,560
I love Neen so much, Natee.

248
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:11,240
So much that…

249
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:15,680
I don't think I'll ever love anyone else
the same way again.

250
00:16:16,640 --> 00:16:18,120
But the more I love her…

251
00:16:18,680 --> 00:16:20,120
the more I realize something.

252
00:16:20,360 --> 00:16:23,160
I'm the reason

253
00:16:23,800 --> 00:16:26,520
she's suffering like this. Because of my mom.

254
00:16:28,080 --> 00:16:29,960
I didn't ask for a divorce

255
00:16:30,280 --> 00:16:32,760
because I stopped loving Neen.

256
00:16:33,480 --> 00:16:34,760
It's because…

257
00:16:36,360 --> 00:16:37,960
I love her too much.

258
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:40,800
I love her enough…

259
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:45,400
to be the one who walks away.

260
00:16:48,560 --> 00:16:50,640
So she won't keep getting hurt because of me.

261
00:17:07,359 --> 00:17:09,079
You're back early, honey.

262
00:17:10,079 --> 00:17:13,000
That woman… she made Runch kick me out.

263
00:17:13,520 --> 00:17:15,800
You and Neen fought again?

264
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:18,960
I've told you so many times not to do this.

265
00:17:19,560 --> 00:17:22,400
You're always like this.
And don't say I didn't warn you

266
00:17:22,480 --> 00:17:24,160
when Runch finally snaps one day.

267
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:25,760
She's not the type to complain…

268
00:17:25,960 --> 00:17:28,840
but once she reaches her limit, you'll regret it.

269
00:17:29,320 --> 00:17:31,440
Runch has changed ever since she got married.

270
00:17:31,440 --> 00:17:34,480
This is exactly why I was against their marriage.

271
00:17:34,800 --> 00:17:37,600
I don't see anything wrong with Neen.

272
00:17:37,840 --> 00:17:39,440
Not you too, Pong.

273
00:17:39,440 --> 00:17:41,680
Why are you defending your daughter-in-law?

274
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:43,400
And stop with the empty threats.

275
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:46,920
Runch can be angry all she wants,
but I'm still her mother.

276
00:17:47,680 --> 00:17:49,000
You're too sure about that.

277
00:17:49,080 --> 00:17:51,240
Once people start their own family,

278
00:17:51,240 --> 00:17:54,320
that family becomes their priority.

279
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:57,440
That's why I never wanted Runch to get married.

280
00:17:59,440 --> 00:18:01,840
No. You just wanted her
to marry someone you liked.

281
00:18:01,840 --> 00:18:04,320
At least I'd have peace of mind

282
00:18:04,320 --> 00:18:06,400
if she married someone I actually got along with.

283
00:18:06,400 --> 00:18:10,920
You've been picking at Neen
ever since they started dating,

284
00:18:10,920 --> 00:18:13,760
just because you never approved of her.

285
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:16,480
And now that she's finally standing up
for herself,

286
00:18:16,480 --> 00:18:18,640
you're making her out to be the villain.

287
00:18:19,520 --> 00:18:23,000
Am I wrong about her, though?
Everything I said is true.

288
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:25,000
She's just some spoiled rich girl

289
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:27,040
who's dragging Runch down with her.

290
00:18:27,040 --> 00:18:28,640
No decent woman

291
00:18:28,640 --> 00:18:30,400
dresses that revealingly.

292
00:18:30,640 --> 00:18:32,640
And her extravagant lifestyle and nightlife?

293
00:18:32,640 --> 00:18:34,120
I can tell she's no good.

294
00:18:34,120 --> 00:18:37,560
I don't care how rich she is.
She's not good enough for our daughter.

295
00:18:37,560 --> 00:18:40,280
She's never brought anything good
into Runch's life. Ugh!

296
00:19:08,520 --> 00:19:11,160
My mom invited us to dinner tonight.

297
00:19:11,320 --> 00:19:12,880
Just the usual family gathering.

298
00:19:13,320 --> 00:19:16,200
I can go alone if you don't want to come.

299
00:19:16,760 --> 00:19:19,320
I never said I didn't want to go.

300
00:19:21,960 --> 00:19:23,960
My parents would understand.

301
00:19:24,120 --> 00:19:26,400
They already know we're getting divorced.

302
00:19:26,960 --> 00:19:31,680
You don't have to pretend in front of them.

303
00:19:39,240 --> 00:19:40,880
We're not divorced yet.

304
00:19:41,640 --> 00:19:44,560
Can't I have dinner with my in-laws?

305
00:19:46,720 --> 00:19:47,800
Whatever.

306
00:19:58,320 --> 00:20:02,480
If you weren't so stubborn,
maybe she wouldn't have asked for a divorce.

307
00:20:02,520 --> 00:20:04,840
Can you not rub it in right now?

308
00:20:05,720 --> 00:20:09,560
Look, things would probably be better
if you softened up a little.

309
00:20:09,560 --> 00:20:13,400
You both know what I've had to put up with,
and you still keep taking her side?

310
00:20:13,840 --> 00:20:15,720
Her mom insults me nonstop.

311
00:20:15,720 --> 00:20:18,200
She even drags my family into it.

312
00:20:18,200 --> 00:20:20,400
And Runch never stands up for me.

313
00:20:20,400 --> 00:20:23,520
Come on, she's stuck in the middle too.

314
00:20:23,720 --> 00:20:25,120
So what?

315
00:20:25,120 --> 00:20:27,760
My own family has never treated me like that.

316
00:20:27,760 --> 00:20:31,080
They didn't raise me
just to get bullied by that hag, okay?

317
00:20:31,080 --> 00:20:32,640
This is hard for me too!

318
00:20:32,920 --> 00:20:34,560
Says the woman

319
00:20:34,560 --> 00:20:36,960
who keeps calling her mother-in-law a hag.

320
00:20:37,240 --> 00:20:39,400
Ex-mother-in-law, okay? Get it right.

321
00:20:39,400 --> 00:20:41,320
Relax, you're not divorced yet.

322
00:20:41,840 --> 00:20:44,160
We will be. Just wait.

323
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:00,440
Runch, try this.

324
00:21:00,520 --> 00:21:02,520
I made it myself.

325
00:21:02,880 --> 00:21:04,640
-Thank you, Mother.
-Of course.

326
00:21:05,840 --> 00:21:07,480
You should have some too, honey.

327
00:21:07,480 --> 00:21:08,960
-Thanks, Mom.
-Eat up.

328
00:21:09,480 --> 00:21:10,680
Eat up, Runch.

329
00:21:11,320 --> 00:21:14,280
You've gotten thinner lately, haven't you?

330
00:21:16,040 --> 00:21:17,040
Yeah…

331
00:21:17,320 --> 00:21:18,720
is everything okay?

332
00:21:19,200 --> 00:21:21,080
Is your work too stressful?

333
00:21:21,720 --> 00:21:24,160
You're not getting enough rest, right?

334
00:21:26,080 --> 00:21:29,960
You can always tell me
if you're tired or need a break.

335
00:21:31,440 --> 00:21:34,640
We're family too, okay?

336
00:21:36,960 --> 00:21:37,840
Yes, Mother.

337
00:21:42,280 --> 00:21:43,360
Runch…

338
00:21:44,280 --> 00:21:46,200
no matter what happens…

339
00:21:48,200 --> 00:21:50,640
you'll always be like a daughter to me.

340
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:55,280
I love you just as much as my own children.

341
00:22:00,800 --> 00:22:01,920
Thank you.

342
00:22:04,120 --> 00:22:05,040
Eat up.

343
00:22:05,040 --> 00:22:07,080
-Here, try the sour curry.
-Today's a good day.

344
00:22:07,760 --> 00:22:09,880
Let me pour my sister-in-law a drink.

345
00:22:11,240 --> 00:22:12,120
Uh…

346
00:22:13,160 --> 00:22:14,160
Okay.

347
00:22:14,760 --> 00:22:17,040
But just a little, please.

348
00:22:17,960 --> 00:22:18,960
Nai…

349
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:24,080
A strong woman like you
should be able to hold your liquor.

350
00:22:24,080 --> 00:22:26,960
Just a little, okay?

351
00:22:27,280 --> 00:22:29,720
Come on, don't be shy.

352
00:22:30,920 --> 00:22:32,760
Nai, can you not do this right now?

353
00:22:33,360 --> 00:22:34,360
It's okay.

354
00:22:44,880 --> 00:22:45,840
Cheers.

355
00:23:09,960 --> 00:23:11,040
Do it gently.

356
00:23:12,120 --> 00:23:13,640
She's out after just two glasses?

357
00:23:16,240 --> 00:23:19,480
You know Runch is a lightweight,
but you still did that to her.

358
00:23:20,040 --> 00:23:21,120
Can you really blame me?

359
00:23:21,480 --> 00:23:23,800
She had the nerve to bring up the divorce.

360
00:23:24,920 --> 00:23:27,840
That's what she gets for breaking your heart.

361
00:23:27,920 --> 00:23:30,520
Oh, grow up.

362
00:23:33,600 --> 00:23:34,960
After everything…

363
00:23:36,320 --> 00:23:37,760
you still care about her?

364
00:23:42,240 --> 00:23:43,720
When you're finally divorced…

365
00:23:44,720 --> 00:23:46,200
are you really going to be okay?

366
00:23:46,840 --> 00:23:48,000
Think about it.

367
00:24:07,240 --> 00:24:10,720
Why did you go over your limit, huh?

368
00:24:12,920 --> 00:24:15,960
Well, Nai asked me to drink.

369
00:24:16,800 --> 00:24:19,840
I didn't want to be rude.

370
00:24:20,280 --> 00:24:22,000
You're way too polite.

371
00:24:27,720 --> 00:24:28,880
Why are you smiling?

372
00:24:30,520 --> 00:24:35,320
I'm just happy… that you're worried about me.

373
00:24:37,360 --> 00:24:39,920
Don't kid yourself. I'm not worried.

374
00:24:40,160 --> 00:24:41,200
I'm scolding you.

375
00:24:45,480 --> 00:24:47,440
That still makes me happy.

376
00:24:47,840 --> 00:24:51,800
It means you care.

377
00:25:00,480 --> 00:25:02,840
You can go home first, Neen.

378
00:25:03,320 --> 00:25:08,320
I'll call a driver.

379
00:25:08,800 --> 00:25:09,720
Ah…

380
00:25:11,600 --> 00:25:14,440
You're not calling anyone. We're going together.

381
00:25:15,040 --> 00:25:16,280
-Oh?
-Come here.

382
00:25:17,240 --> 00:25:18,600
Leave the car here.

383
00:25:18,600 --> 00:25:21,480
I'll have my dad's driver
bring it to our place tomorrow.

384
00:25:22,760 --> 00:25:27,080
You're the best, Neen.

385
00:25:27,240 --> 00:25:28,360
Ugh…

386
00:25:40,320 --> 00:25:41,640
You're in your room now.

387
00:25:56,800 --> 00:25:57,840
Stop…

388
00:25:58,320 --> 00:26:00,240
we're not like that anymore.

389
00:26:01,280 --> 00:26:02,920
Why not?

390
00:26:03,520 --> 00:26:05,320
I remember…

391
00:26:06,000 --> 00:26:08,200
you used to like it.

392
00:26:08,680 --> 00:26:10,280
Because now we're not…

393
00:26:14,040 --> 00:26:17,000
We're not like that anymore.

394
00:26:18,120 --> 00:26:19,360
Don't do this again.

395
00:26:57,920 --> 00:26:59,080
Thank you.

396
00:27:25,800 --> 00:27:26,840
Oh, come on…

397
00:27:31,040 --> 00:27:32,680
What's wrong with your car?

398
00:27:34,320 --> 00:27:36,720
It won't start. Battery's dead.

399
00:27:37,280 --> 00:27:38,720
And I've got a meeting today.

400
00:27:41,120 --> 00:27:42,720
In that case…

401
00:27:43,440 --> 00:27:44,720
just get in my car.

402
00:27:45,280 --> 00:27:46,680
I'll drive you.

403
00:28:01,200 --> 00:28:03,840
I'm getting coffee. You want anything?

404
00:28:04,000 --> 00:28:04,840
No.

405
00:28:42,040 --> 00:28:44,640
What is there to talk about? It's just coffee.

406
00:28:47,400 --> 00:28:48,440
Babe…

407
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:52,200
what's taking you so long?

408
00:28:52,280 --> 00:28:55,760
Oh, there were a few people in line ahead of me.

409
00:28:56,200 --> 00:28:58,760
Then why didn't you tell me?

410
00:28:58,760 --> 00:29:00,680
I was bored waiting.

411
00:29:00,960 --> 00:29:04,240
You should make it up to me, you know.

412
00:29:06,640 --> 00:29:08,160
How?

413
00:29:09,120 --> 00:29:12,200
You know… the usual.

414
00:29:17,280 --> 00:29:19,040
Come on, babe.

415
00:29:21,640 --> 00:29:24,000
Aww, you're so sweet.

416
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:26,040
My darling is the best.

417
00:29:26,640 --> 00:29:28,080
Ms. Runch, your drink is ready.

418
00:29:28,560 --> 00:29:30,120
-Thank you.
-Oh.

419
00:29:30,320 --> 00:29:31,880
Thank you very much.

420
00:29:34,720 --> 00:29:36,000
Let's go, babe.

421
00:29:44,480 --> 00:29:46,120
Did you just get jealous?

422
00:29:46,200 --> 00:29:47,120
I wasn't jealous.

423
00:29:47,560 --> 00:29:48,720
I was just annoyed.

424
00:29:48,880 --> 00:29:51,960
You seem pretty familiar with them…
You must come here a lot.

425
00:29:52,120 --> 00:29:54,160
I do. I come here every day.

426
00:29:54,160 --> 00:29:57,280
Tch. Now I'm wondering
if you're really here for coffee.

427
00:29:58,320 --> 00:30:00,080
I'm here for coffee, of course.

428
00:30:00,600 --> 00:30:03,640
There are so many other coffee shops.
Why does it have to be this one?

429
00:30:04,440 --> 00:30:05,440
Look…

430
00:30:06,400 --> 00:30:10,520
You really don't remember?
This is our special place.

431
00:30:50,440 --> 00:30:51,520
Thanks for the ride.

432
00:31:03,560 --> 00:31:06,840
Let me help you carry your things.
You brought a lot.

433
00:31:06,840 --> 00:31:07,720
No need.

434
00:31:09,360 --> 00:31:10,320
I'll help.

435
00:31:10,880 --> 00:31:12,360
Just let me.

436
00:31:25,040 --> 00:31:26,840
Hello, Ms. Neen.

437
00:31:26,840 --> 00:31:27,600
Hello.

438
00:31:27,600 --> 00:31:29,200
-Hello, Ms. Runch.
-Hello.

439
00:31:29,360 --> 00:31:32,320
Well, it's been a while since I last saw you.

440
00:31:32,520 --> 00:31:33,360
Oh…

441
00:31:33,640 --> 00:31:37,320
I've just been busy with work lately.

442
00:31:37,320 --> 00:31:38,200
I see.

443
00:31:38,360 --> 00:31:41,200
That's good to hear. I was worried

444
00:31:41,400 --> 00:31:42,960
you two might have had a fight.

445
00:31:45,040 --> 00:31:48,960
You know, I really look up to you both.

446
00:31:49,160 --> 00:31:51,000
Everyone here sees you

447
00:31:51,000 --> 00:31:53,120
as the ideal couple.

448
00:32:13,560 --> 00:32:16,240
I'll have your car fixed for you.

449
00:32:16,480 --> 00:32:18,600
I'll pick you up this evening.

450
00:32:19,240 --> 00:32:20,120
No need.

451
00:32:21,080 --> 00:32:22,880
I can get my own ride.

452
00:32:24,680 --> 00:32:25,680
That won't do.

453
00:32:30,480 --> 00:32:34,000
Don't forget… we're everyone's ideal couple.

454
00:32:34,800 --> 00:32:36,960
We can't disappoint them.

455
00:32:37,600 --> 00:32:38,880
See you this evening, okay?

456
00:32:55,520 --> 00:32:56,560
I'm telling you,

457
00:32:56,880 --> 00:32:59,640
if Runch hadn't married the owner's granddaughter,

458
00:32:59,640 --> 00:33:02,920
there's no way she'd be our boss.

459
00:33:02,920 --> 00:33:03,800
Exactly.

460
00:33:03,800 --> 00:33:08,040
She makes mistakes sometimes,
but no one dares say anything.

461
00:33:09,160 --> 00:33:12,200
What kind of boss dumps work
on her team like that?

462
00:33:12,680 --> 00:33:14,640
And she never says anything in meetings.

463
00:33:14,640 --> 00:33:18,480
Just sits there like a prop to make the company
look more progressive.

464
00:33:18,720 --> 00:33:20,400
I wonder…

465
00:33:20,600 --> 00:33:22,440
is she actually capable, or is it just because

466
00:33:22,880 --> 00:33:24,600
her partner is the Iperis heir?

467
00:33:26,000 --> 00:33:27,200
Who knows.

468
00:33:27,440 --> 00:33:30,480
But if I were her, I'd feel pretty insecure.

469
00:33:30,720 --> 00:33:33,120
Even after marrying into the owner's family,

470
00:33:33,120 --> 00:33:35,720
she's still just a figurehead.

471
00:33:35,800 --> 00:33:37,400
Nobody really respects her.

472
00:33:37,440 --> 00:33:40,440
Yeah. When she walks by,
everyone just goes quiet and works.

473
00:33:40,440 --> 00:33:42,200
No one really talks to her.

474
00:33:42,200 --> 00:33:44,440
She probably doesn't get along with anyone.

475
00:33:45,520 --> 00:33:47,600
Maybe she knows

476
00:33:47,600 --> 00:33:49,440
she's not that capable,

477
00:33:49,520 --> 00:33:51,520
so she just keeps to herself.

478
00:33:51,920 --> 00:33:53,720
Hiding it, you know?

479
00:34:06,840 --> 00:34:08,159
Oh… Boss.

480
00:34:09,760 --> 00:34:10,719
Coffee?

481
00:34:44,840 --> 00:34:47,880
They said it's the electrical system.

482
00:34:48,239 --> 00:34:50,719
It'll take a few days to fix.

483
00:34:51,000 --> 00:34:53,199
I'll drive you for now.

484
00:34:54,000 --> 00:34:54,920
You don't have to.

485
00:34:56,320 --> 00:34:59,960
I'll ask my dad for a spare car.
No need to trouble yourself.

486
00:35:00,920 --> 00:35:04,680
It's not trouble if it's for you.

487
00:35:14,600 --> 00:35:16,000
This isn't the way home.

488
00:35:18,280 --> 00:35:21,120
Let's eat first. Then we'll go home.

489
00:35:33,400 --> 00:35:35,920
I ordered your favorite.

490
00:35:36,200 --> 00:35:37,360
Eat up, okay?

491
00:35:38,400 --> 00:35:39,640
Why are you doing this?

492
00:35:41,160 --> 00:35:42,280
What do you mean?

493
00:35:43,040 --> 00:35:45,960
No one here knows us.
So why are you being nice to me?

494
00:35:46,000 --> 00:35:48,800
I just want to do things for you like I used to.

495
00:35:49,000 --> 00:35:52,160
Like before? When nothing is the same anymore?

496
00:35:53,400 --> 00:35:54,520
What do you want from me?

497
00:35:54,560 --> 00:35:57,600
Are you trying to mess with my feelings?

498
00:35:58,000 --> 00:35:59,520
That's not what I'm doing.

499
00:36:00,600 --> 00:36:04,040
I just want us to separate on good terms.

500
00:36:04,520 --> 00:36:05,480
There's no need.

501
00:36:05,800 --> 00:36:09,520
You already ruined every good memory I had
the moment you brought up divorce.

502
00:36:09,920 --> 00:36:13,600
So stop being nice to me.
Stop acting like you still know me.

503
00:36:14,240 --> 00:36:17,040
I don't want to get used to you
being by my side again.

504
00:37:41,280 --> 00:37:43,280
You probably don't want to see me,

505
00:37:43,560 --> 00:37:45,000
so I've headed to work.

506
00:37:45,440 --> 00:37:47,120
Don't forget to eat this, okay?

507
00:37:47,240 --> 00:37:48,120
From Runch.

508
00:37:58,960 --> 00:38:00,880
You really know me so well…

509
00:38:17,280 --> 00:38:21,000
♪ In the moments when we look at each other ♪

510
00:38:21,000 --> 00:38:23,920
♪ Even if I don't say it out loud ♪

511
00:38:23,920 --> 00:38:27,560
♪ Deep inside, I only care about you ♪

512
00:38:27,560 --> 00:38:31,040
♪ Love is so magical ♪

513
00:38:32,200 --> 00:38:35,960
♪ Even though sometimes I don't treat you right ♪

514
00:38:36,000 --> 00:38:38,760
♪ And there aren't many sweet words ♪

515
00:38:38,760 --> 00:38:41,160
♪ But I want you to know that ♪

516
00:38:41,160 --> 00:38:45,800
♪ My life partner will always be you ♪

517
00:38:45,840 --> 00:38:49,640
♪ I'm weak for your lips ♪

518
00:38:49,640 --> 00:38:53,640
♪ And the kiss upon my forehead ♪

519
00:38:53,640 --> 00:38:59,600
♪ Every action conveys these words, you know? ♪

520
00:39:00,400 --> 00:39:04,160
♪ Can you hear me saying I love you? ♪

521
00:39:04,160 --> 00:39:07,960
♪ My love is in these soft whispers ♪

522
00:39:07,960 --> 00:39:10,200
♪ You have to feel it with your heart ♪

523
00:39:10,200 --> 00:39:15,360
♪ Our touches will make you understand ♪

524
00:39:15,400 --> 00:39:18,880
♪ Can you hear me saying I love you? ♪

525
00:39:18,880 --> 00:39:20,800
♪ Use the feeling you know ♪

526
00:39:20,800 --> 00:39:24,960
♪ And you'll love so deeply ♪

527
00:39:24,960 --> 00:39:26,960
♪ Can you feel my love? ♪

528
00:39:26,960 --> 00:39:30,800
That's the one.
I have it in blue, but not in pink yet.

529
00:39:30,800 --> 00:39:32,480
-Then you have to get it.
-Yeah.

530
00:39:32,520 --> 00:39:33,800
-It's gorgeous.
-And it's 10% off too.

531
00:39:33,800 --> 00:39:36,040
-Look at that one.
-Oh, that's pretty.

532
00:39:36,040 --> 00:39:36,920
Right?

533
00:39:36,920 --> 00:39:39,400
-Should we go take a look?
-Oh? Isn't that Neen?

534
00:39:40,840 --> 00:39:42,520
Yeah.

535
00:39:42,800 --> 00:39:45,360
Ging, isn't that your beautiful daughter-in-law?

536
00:39:45,360 --> 00:39:46,360
Probably not.

537
00:39:46,360 --> 00:39:47,800
-No, that's definitely her.
-Hello!

538
00:39:47,800 --> 00:39:48,600
Hi, Neen!

539
00:39:50,920 --> 00:39:53,080
Hello, everyone.

540
00:39:53,080 --> 00:39:54,440
-Hello.
-Hello.

541
00:39:54,440 --> 00:39:56,400
So nice to see you.

542
00:39:56,400 --> 00:39:58,720
You've gotten even prettier.

543
00:39:58,800 --> 00:39:59,800
Thank you.

544
00:40:00,080 --> 00:40:01,160
Oh, Neen,

545
00:40:01,320 --> 00:40:03,120
Ging was saying she wanted this designer scarf.

546
00:40:03,120 --> 00:40:05,720
She really likes it, but it's expensive.

547
00:40:05,720 --> 00:40:07,640
-That's 35,000 baht.
-Hey…

548
00:40:07,680 --> 00:40:09,160
Do you think you could get it for her?

549
00:40:09,320 --> 00:40:10,440
Of course.

550
00:40:10,680 --> 00:40:11,560
You really don't have to.

551
00:40:12,200 --> 00:40:14,120
I want to, Mother.

552
00:40:14,200 --> 00:40:16,560
You're Runch's mother.

553
00:40:16,600 --> 00:40:18,960
Of course I should treat you well.

554
00:40:19,000 --> 00:40:20,240
Please don't hold back.

555
00:40:21,000 --> 00:40:23,640
You're so kind, Neen.

556
00:40:23,640 --> 00:40:25,960
That's your perfect daughter-in-law.

557
00:40:27,520 --> 00:40:28,320
Right?

558
00:40:31,320 --> 00:40:33,040
-Isn't she just the sweetest?
-Yeah.

559
00:40:33,840 --> 00:40:35,280
Here you go, Mother.

560
00:40:38,840 --> 00:40:42,640
Don't worry, I'm happy to buy it for you.

561
00:40:45,640 --> 00:40:47,600
Oh, and one more thing…

562
00:40:48,200 --> 00:40:49,920
Since everyone's here,

563
00:40:49,920 --> 00:40:52,200
I got something for both of you too.

564
00:40:52,200 --> 00:40:54,200
Oh no, dear, we couldn't possibly…

565
00:40:54,200 --> 00:40:56,000
Please, you have to accept them.

566
00:40:56,040 --> 00:40:58,520
-Wow…
-Thank you so much, Neen.

567
00:40:58,760 --> 00:41:02,120
I'll treasure this.

568
00:41:02,760 --> 00:41:04,920
Are you all going somewhere after this?

569
00:41:04,920 --> 00:41:06,520
We're having lunch together.

570
00:41:06,520 --> 00:41:08,120
Lunch?

571
00:41:12,920 --> 00:41:14,040
Mother,

572
00:41:14,200 --> 00:41:15,560
please take this.

573
00:41:18,320 --> 00:41:20,560
Treat yourself and your friends to something nice.

574
00:41:21,040 --> 00:41:22,920
Please order whatever you like.

575
00:41:22,920 --> 00:41:25,520
It's my treat. Don't hold back.

576
00:41:28,840 --> 00:41:31,840
I have somewhere else to be,
so I'll excuse myself now.

577
00:41:32,120 --> 00:41:32,920
Goodbye.

578
00:41:33,000 --> 00:41:34,400
-Goodbye, dear.
-Goodbye.

579
00:41:34,640 --> 00:41:39,080
You're so lucky to have Neen as a daughter-in-law.

580
00:41:39,080 --> 00:41:40,040
Yeah.

581
00:41:42,400 --> 00:41:44,080
I've always wanted this one.

582
00:41:53,920 --> 00:41:55,640
-Oh, Mom--
-Peeracha!

583
00:41:55,880 --> 00:41:57,040
Come out here!

584
00:41:57,280 --> 00:41:58,600
Get out here right now!

585
00:42:00,640 --> 00:42:02,000
What's going on, Mom?

586
00:42:03,000 --> 00:42:06,240
Ask your sneaky little wife what she did!

587
00:42:08,880 --> 00:42:10,960
You humiliated me in front of my friends.

588
00:42:11,040 --> 00:42:14,200
Made me look like I'm living off your money!

589
00:42:16,600 --> 00:42:18,120
What did I do wrong?

590
00:42:18,200 --> 00:42:21,880
I was just helping an old woman
so she wouldn't starve to death.

591
00:42:23,040 --> 00:42:24,880
Mom, please. Let's talk outside.

592
00:42:25,320 --> 00:42:26,400
Stay out of this!

593
00:42:26,400 --> 00:42:28,240
-Mom! Come with me!
-Runch!

594
00:42:28,240 --> 00:42:30,040
Did you just raise your voice at me?!

595
00:42:30,040 --> 00:42:32,240
Has she already turned you against me?!

596
00:42:32,240 --> 00:42:33,600
Ugh, you're such a nuisance!

597
00:42:35,400 --> 00:42:36,080
Mom!

598
00:42:54,800 --> 00:42:55,760
Neen…

599
00:43:10,760 --> 00:43:11,600
Mom…

600
00:43:14,120 --> 00:43:15,200
come with me.

601
00:43:19,000 --> 00:43:19,840
Now.

602
00:43:24,040 --> 00:43:25,040
Runch…

603
00:43:25,640 --> 00:43:26,600
Runch…

604
00:43:28,640 --> 00:43:30,440
Runch, I didn't mean it…

605
00:43:56,720 --> 00:43:59,080
THREE YEARS AGO

606
00:44:08,040 --> 00:44:10,920
That's a pretty big stain.
Maybe you should change your shirt.

607
00:44:11,480 --> 00:44:12,480
It's okay.

608
00:44:13,080 --> 00:44:16,800
I'm almost off work anyway.
And I don't have a spare.

609
00:44:17,960 --> 00:44:21,440
A wet shirt can be kind of revealing, you know?

610
00:44:21,960 --> 00:44:24,280
If you don't mind, you can borrow mine.

611
00:44:24,280 --> 00:44:25,680
I haven't worn it yet.

612
00:44:35,080 --> 00:44:36,720
I don't want to trouble you.

613
00:44:41,960 --> 00:44:43,760
It's fine.
Please take it.

614
00:44:44,840 --> 00:44:47,280
Walking around in a wet shirt feels awful.

615
00:44:48,760 --> 00:44:50,360
I'll go grab it from my car.

616
00:45:04,960 --> 00:45:06,160
Thank you.

617
00:45:06,720 --> 00:45:08,320
I'll wash it and return it to you soon.

618
00:45:09,200 --> 00:45:10,560
May I…

619
00:45:11,800 --> 00:45:13,560
have your email?

620
00:45:13,960 --> 00:45:14,960
My email?

621
00:45:16,520 --> 00:45:18,440
Wouldn't a phone number be easier?

622
00:45:19,480 --> 00:45:20,520
Here.

623
00:45:26,000 --> 00:45:29,160
Done. I'm Neen. And you are?

624
00:45:29,880 --> 00:45:30,960
Runch.

625
00:45:31,560 --> 00:45:32,920
Do you work around here?

626
00:45:33,240 --> 00:45:34,480
Somewhere nearby.

627
00:45:35,400 --> 00:45:37,120
Nice to meet you, Runch.

628
00:46:30,320 --> 00:46:32,960
She thinks having connections and a rich wife

629
00:46:32,960 --> 00:46:34,800
makes her untouchable?

630
00:46:34,800 --> 00:46:36,440
Be a man.

631
00:46:36,640 --> 00:46:39,120
There are plenty of ways

632
00:46:39,120 --> 00:46:41,360
to make people think we're in love.

633
00:46:41,560 --> 00:46:42,880
Let's do all of them.

634
00:46:44,360 --> 00:46:46,120
You know Neen hates me.

635
00:46:46,120 --> 00:46:48,200
And I know you hate her too.

636
00:46:49,720 --> 00:46:50,840
-Come here.
-Huh?

637
00:46:50,840 --> 00:46:52,440
-Ugh!
-Stop it…

638
00:46:55,560 --> 00:46:58,160
♪ Living with pain and love ♪

639
00:46:58,160 --> 00:47:00,920
♪ Living while waiting and losing hope ♪

640
00:47:00,920 --> 00:47:03,360
♪ A voice inside my heart says enough ♪

641
00:47:03,360 --> 00:47:06,520
♪ But another voice asks me to endure ♪

642
00:47:06,520 --> 00:47:09,160
♪ I stay because I love you, you know? ♪

643
00:47:09,160 --> 00:47:15,360
♪ I still believe in the love between us ♪

644
00:47:15,600 --> 00:47:20,000
♪ Please let us go back to how we were ♪

645
00:47:20,000 --> 00:47:24,200
♪ I don't know if our love is just impossible ♪

646
00:47:24,200 --> 00:47:27,040
♪ Or if there's a reason for all of this ♪

647
00:47:27,040 --> 00:47:31,240
♪ And that reason is you don't love me ♪
